2 unit(s) Beyond Meat®
1 unit(s) Black Beans
113 g Mirepoix
1 unit(s) Green Onion
2 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
4 tbsp Tomato Sauce Base
¼ cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
1 unit(s) Sour Cream
1 tbsp Mexican Seasoning
1 tbsp Tex-Mex Paste
1 unit(s) Chicken Broth Concentrate
0.13 tsp Pepper*
0.13 tsp Salt*
1 tbsp Oil*

Drain and rinse black beans.
Thinly slice green onions.
Peel, then mince or grate garlic.

Heat a large pot over medium-high heat.
When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then Beyond Meat® patties, garlic and mirepoix. Season with Mexican Seasoning, salt and pepper.
Cook, breaking up patties into smaller pieces, until crispy, 5-6 min.**

Add Tex-Mex paste, black beans, tomato sauce base, broth concentrate and 1 3/4 cups (2 1/2 cups) water to the pot, then stir to combine.
Bring to a boil.

Once boiling, reduce heat to medium-low.
Cook uncovered, stirring occasionally, until chili thickens slightly, 8-10 min. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Divide chili between bowls.
Dollop sour cream over top.
Sprinkle cheese and green onions over top.

If you've opted to get Beyond Meat®, cook it the same way as the turkey, breaking up patties into smaller pieces, until crispy, 5-6 min.**